He claims SeaWorld was more concerned with training its staff in how to respond to “sceptical guests” than in encouraging scientific research. “You got media training on how to deflect awkward questions – told how to put a positive spin on things,” he says. He felt intimidated and was convinced that if he complained he’d be punished by being moved to work with the sea lions.
